[normal]26.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Defence Committees have taken a keen interest for many years in the operation and effectiveness of the Service complaints process and the work of the Service Complaints Commissioner for the Armed Forces which was established under the Armed Forces Act 2006
[normal]. 
[normal]We
[normal] conducted a
[normal]n
[normal]  inquiry into the work of the Commissioner, concluding that there was a lack of confidence among Service personnel in the complaints system and that the system was not working effectively or efficiently. 
[normal]We
[normal] also examined the role of the C
[normal]ommissioner and recommended that the 
[normal]role
[normal] should change to
[normal] that of
[normal] an Armed Forces Ombudsman. As a consequence of 
[normal]our
[normal] report and the Commissioner’s annual report, discussions are ongoing between the MoD and the Commissioner to revise her role and to improv
[normal]e the efficiency and effectiveness of the Service complaints system.
